Italian President Francesco Cossiga askedveteran Christian Democrat politician Giulio Andreotti to tryto form a new government, officials said.    They said Andreotti had reserved his reply on whether toaccept the mandate, normal procedure until he has ascertainedwhether he can form a government.    Cossiga nominated Andreotti, sole candidate of the majorityChristian Democrats, despite stiff opposition from theSocialists of outgoing Prime Minister Bettino Craxi. REUTER&#3;